te code modifications, terminal command execution, and dependency installation without real-time monitoring\n\n### Other Recent Features:\n- **Multi-Agent Parallel Processing** - Support for up to 8 simultaneous agents based on Git worktree isolation\n- **Local Model Deployment** - For improved privacy and speed\n- **Code Tracing & AI Generation Marking** - For team collaboration and quality control\n- **Multi-modal Support** - Image recognition and UI prototype generation\n\n## Previous Major Releases\n\n### **Cursor 1.0** (June 2025)\n- **BugBot** - Automatic code review tool for GitHub PRs\n- **Memories** - Conversation context retention\n- **One-click MCP Configuration**\n- **Jupyter Notebook Support**\n- **Background Agent** - Fully available to all users\n\n### **Cursor 0.5** (May 2025)\n- **Max Mode** - Enhanced context support with transparent token-based pricing\n- **New Tab Model** - Multi-file intelligent code suggestions\n- **Enhanced Inline Editing** - Improved editing with agent handoff capabilities\n- **Chat Upgrades** - Export to markdown, copy chats for parallel exploration\n\n---\n\n**Important Note:** The February 2026 information comes from Chinese tech articles published in February 2026. For the most authoritative and up-to-date information, I recommend checking Cursor's official channels:\n\n- Official website: https://cursor.sh/\n- Cursor's official blog\n- Cursor's release notes or changelog\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about any of these features?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
