ajor updates throughout 2025:\n\n- **Wave 8 (May 2025):** Enterprise-focused features including GitHub PR review automation, Google Docs context integration, and conversation sharing\n\n- **Wave 6 (April 2025):** One-click deployment, intelligent commit features, and memory enhancements\n\n- **Wave 4 (March 2025):** Preview functionality, \"point and modify\" capabilities, tab-to-import features, and linter integration\n\n- **Wave 3 (February 2025):** New AI model integrations (DeepSeek-v3, DeepSeek-R1, o3-mini, Gemini 2.0 Flash)\n\n## Key Features of Windsurf\n\n- **Flow Technology:** Combines collaborative Copilots with autonomous agents for deep code understanding\n- **Cascade Assistant:** Intelligent code suggestions and real-time developer operation response\n- **Multi-file context understanding** and support for various AI models (GPT-5, Claude Sonnet 4 mentioned)\n- **Free tier available** with advanced features for paying customers\n\n## Note on February 2026\n\nSince we're currently in 2025, any February 2026 updates would be in the future. The information found refers to releases from late 2025 (December 2025/February 2026 timeframe mentions). For the most current and accurate information about Windsurf releases, I recommend checking their official blog at codeium.com/blog.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
