n- Rolling out to multi-tier subscribers\n\n### ⚡ **GPT-5.3-Codex Model Upgrade**\n- **Date**: February 11, 2026\n- OpenAI's latest **GPT-5.3-Codex** model began rolling out\n- **25% performance improvement** in agentic coding tasks over GPT-5.2-Codex\n- Significantly reduces execution wait times for complex, long-running workflows\n- Available for Pro, Pro+, Business, and Enterprise users\n- Supports VS Code, GitHub web, mobile, CLI, and Coding Agent environments\n- Enterprise admins must manually enable the feature in settings\n\n### 🌟 **Agent Mode Integration**\n- GitHub Copilot officially integrated **agent technology**\n- New agent capabilities include:\n  - Autonomous code iteration\n  - Intelligent error identification and correction\n  - Multi-file code refactoring\n  - Self-healing compilation errors\n\n### 📝 **Copilot Edits Feature**\n- Allows developers to handle multiple files simultaneously in the editor\n- Provides code modification suggestions directly within the editing interface\n- Offers a more convenient code review pathway\n\n### 🖼️ **Visual Capabilities Enhanced**\n- Support for uploading screenshots, photos, and charts\n- Can generate interfaces, code, and alt text based on visual input files\n- Significantly expands application scenarios\n\n### 💡 **Next Edit Suggestions**\n- Analyzes recent edits and predicts next developer actions\n- Provides more intelligent editing recommendations\n\n## Context\nThese updates come just 10 days after the GPT-5.3-Codex integration and are seen as a direct response to Anthropic Claude Opus 4.6, demonstrating GitHub's multi-model strategy to consolidate its position in the AI coding assistant market.\n\nThe updates particularly benefit developers working on architecture design and automated refactoring, representing a shift from \"AI assistance\" to \"AI engineer\" capabilities.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
