language Response Configuration** - Language settings support\n4. **Session Transfer (/teleport)** - Move sessions between devices seamlessly\n5. **Multi-line Input** - Shift+Enter for line breaks (no configuration needed)\n6. **Asynchronous Sub-agents** - Parallel task processing\n7. **MCP Dynamic Updates** - Model Context Protocol enhancements\n8. **Checkpoint System** - Quick undo with Esc+Esc or /rewind command\n\n#### Version Jump:\n- From **2.0.76** → **2.1.1** (then to 2.1.4)\n- Breaking update with no backward compatibility issues\n\n### 📝 **Claude Opus 4.6 Integration** (February 12, 2026)\nRecent update shows integration with Claude Opus 4.6 featuring:\n- **200K context window** (expandable to 1M tokens in beta)\n- **128K token maximum output** (doubled from previous version)\n- **Adaptive thinking mechanism** - adjusts reasoning depth based on complexity\n- **Context compression** - intelligent summarization for continuous conversations\n- **New \"max effort\" parameter** - user-controlled compute resource allocation\n\n## Installation\n```bash\nnpm update -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n# Or specific version:\nnpm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code@2.1.1\n```\n\n## Impact\nDevelopers report up to **10x efficiency improvements** in their workflows. The update marks Claude Code's evolution from a pure command-line tool to a mature development platform.\n\n---\n\n**Note:** My search didn't find specific February 2026 releases beyond the Opus 4.6 integration. Most major feature updates occurred in January 2026. For the most current information, I'd recommend checking the official GitHub repository's CHANGELOG.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
