iling the core mechanism of the local agent Codex CLI\n- The \"agent loop\" mechanism achieves automated programming interaction through:\n  - Command parsing\n  - Model reasoning\n  - Tool calling closed loop\n\n**3. Enhanced Capabilities (February 2026)**\nBased on the search results, the new Codex system features:\n- **Model**: Based on GPT-5.2-Codex model\n- **Performance**: 40% improvement in reasoning speed\n- **Input capacity**: Support for 400,000 tokens\n- **Language support**: 50+ programming languages\n- **Integration**: MCP protocol integration and \"work tree\" mechanism\n- **Multi-agent support**: Parallel execution and automated workflow execution\n- **Project-level understanding**: Can handle UI design, backend architecture, and bug scanning tasks\n\n### Competitive Positioning:\n- OpenAI is positioning Codex as an \"AI collaborator\" rather than just code completion\n- The system competes with Anthropic's Claude Code\n- Offers double rate quotas, free user access, and an \"Agent Command Center\" paradigm to attract developers\n\n### Installation:\nThe current version can be installed via:\n```bash\nnpm install -g @openai/codex\n```\n\n**Note**: The search results primarily cover announcements from January-February 2026, with specific detailed release notes for February 2026 features not fully documented in the available sources. For the most up-to-date technical specifications and release notes, I recommend checking OpenAI's official GitHub repository or documentation.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
