      "Based on my search results, I need to clarify an important finding: **I did not find any specific information about Gemini CLI updates released in February 2026**. \n\nHowever, I found relevant information about recent Gemini CLI updates. Here's what I discovered:\n\n## Key Findings\n\n### Most Recent Updates (Around December 2025 - January 2026)\n\n**Gemini CLI V0.22 Release (December 2025)**\n- **Gemini 3 Series Models** made available to all Free Tier users\n- New models include: Gemini 3 Pro and Gemini 3 Flash\n- Requires version 0.22.0 or higher\n- To use: Update CLI, enable \"Preview Features\" in settings, switch to \"Auto (Gemini 3)\" model\n\n**New Extensions Released:**\n- **Conductor**: Transforms Gemini CLI into an active project manager that follows protocols to specify, plan, and implement software features and bug fixes\n- **Endor Labs**: Another significant extension plugin (details limited)\n\n### Earlier Major Updates (July 2025)\n\n**Version 0.1.13 Update** included:\n- Audio and video file support\n- Markdown table rendering\n- Nested Markdown file imports (using @ symbol)\n- New `/privacy` command for privacy settings\n- Integration with VSCodium and Neovim editors\n- Framework upgrades (Ink 6 and React 19)\n- \"Shades of Purple\" theme\n- Enhanced stability and security features\n\n### Installation Information\n\nThe CLI can be installed via:\n- **npm**: `npm install -g @google/gemini-cli`\n- **Homebrew**: `brew install gemini-cli`\n\n**Release Cadence:**\n- Preview releases: Weekly (Tuesdays at UTC 2359)\n- Stable releases: Weekly (Tuesdays at UTC 2000)\n- Nightly builds: Daily\n\n## Summary\n\nWhile I couldn't locate specific February 2026 updates (which may be because they haven't occurred yet or aren't widely documented), the most recent significant updates were the **V0.22 release in December 2025** that opened Gemini 3 models to free users and introduced new extension plugins.\n\nFor the absolute latest information, I recommend checking the [official GitHub repository](https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli)."
